---
import SiteLayout from '@layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import thuptenImage from '../assets/thupten.png';
import jamyangImage from '../assets/jamyang.png';
import sonamImage from '../assets/sonam.jpg';
import collabImage from '../assets/collab.png';
---

<SiteLayout title="About Terma Foundry — Team, Mission & Tibetan Typography" description="Terma Foundry is building the open-source digital infrastructure that Tibetan script has never had — typefaces, rendering tools, and CSS frameworks for 6 million speakers worldwide.">

  <!-- PAGE HEADER -->
  <section class="page-section" style="padding-bottom:2rem;">
    <div class="section-eyebrow reveal">About Us</div>
    <h1 class="section-heading reveal">Tibetan script deserves<br>a digital future.</h1>
    <p class="section-sub reveal">Terma Foundry is building the open-source type and web infrastructure that six million Tibetan speakers have never had — working typefaces, rendering tools, and the world's first CSS framework for Tibetan script.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- OUR STORY -->
  <section class="page-section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="story-grid reveal">
      <div class="story-text">
        <h2>The Gap</h2>
        <p>Tibetan is spoken by over six million people across Tibet, India, Nepal, Bhutan, and diaspora communities worldwide. It has one of the oldest continuous literary traditions on earth. And yet on the modern web, it is effectively invisible — broken by the very tools developers rely on.</p>
        <p>Rendering inconsistencies, vowel mark clipping, line-height collisions, and a near-total absence of display, children's, or UI typefaces have left Tibetan-speaking communities building with tools that were never designed for their script. While Japanese, Korean, and Arabic type ecosystems offer hundreds of high-quality fonts across every register, Tibetan developers navigate a handful of legacy faces and a CSS stack that has no concept of the script's unique requirements.</p>
        <p>This is not a minor inconvenience. It shapes what gets built, what gets published, and who can participate in the digital life of their language. <em>A script that can't render beautifully doesn't get used — and a language that disappears from screens disappears from children.</em></p>

        <!-- TIBETAN TRANSLATION PANEL -->
        <div class="bo-panel" id="bo-panel">
          <button class="bo-toggle" id="bo-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="bo-toggle-script tr-jomolhari tr-guard" lang="bo">བར་སྣང་།</span>
            <span class="bo-toggle-label tr-jomolhari tr-guard" lang="bo">བོད་སྐད་དུ་ཀློག་པ།</span>
            <span class="bo-toggle-chevron" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          </button>
          <div class="bo-body" id="bo-body" hidden>
            <div class="bo-toolbar">
              <label class="bo-font-label" for="bo-font-select">Font</label>
              <select class="bo-font-select" id="bo-font-select">
                <option value="tr-jomolhari">Jomolhari</option>
                <option value="tr-noto">Noto Serif Tibetan</option>
                <option value="tr-machine-uni">Tibetan Machine Uni</option>
                <option value="tr-drutsa">Qomolangma Drutsa</option>
                <option value="tr-monlam">Monlam Bodyig</option>
              </select>
              <span class="bo-powered">rendered by <a href="/termaui" class="bo-powered-link">termaUI</a></span>
            </div>
            <div class="bo-text" id="bo-text">
              <h3 class="bo-heading tr-jomolhari tr-text-xl tr-leading-relaxed tr-guard-lg tr-ligatures" lang="bo">བར་སྣང་།</h3>
              <p class="bo-para tr-jomolhari tr-text-base tr-leading-relaxed tr-guard tr-ligatures" lang="bo">བོད་སྐད་ནི་བོད་དང་རྒྱ་གར། བལ་ཡུལ། འབྲུག་ཡུལ། དེ་བཞིན་འཇིག་རྟེན་ཡོངས་ཀྱི་རྒྱལ་གཞིས་སྤྱི་ཚོགས་ཁྲོད་ཀྱི་མི་ས་ཡ་དྲུག་ལྷག་གིས་བེད་སྤྱོད་བྱེད་བཞིན་ཡོད། འཛམ་གླིང་སྟེང་གི་རྒྱུན་མི་ཆད་པའི་རྩོམ་རིག་གི་སྲོལ་རྒྱུན་རྙིང་ཤོས་ཀྱི་གཅིག་ཡིན། འོན་ཀྱང་དེང་རབས་དྲ་རྒྱ་སྟེང་དུ་བོད་ཡིག་ནི་མཐོང་ཐབས་མེད་པ་ལྟ་བུ་ཆགས་ཡོད། ལས་རིགས་པས་བརྟེན་བཞིན་པའི་ལག་ཆ་དེ་དག་གིས་བོད་ཡིག་ཆག་བཅོས་བྱས་ཡོད།</p>
              <p class="bo-para tr-jomolhari tr-text-base tr-leading-relaxed tr-guard tr-ligatures" lang="bo">མངོན་པར་སྣང་བའི་མི་མཐུན་པ། དབྱངས་ཀྱི་རྟགས་ཀྱི་གཅོད་པ། ཡིག་ཕྲེང་གི་མཐོ་དམའི་འཕྲད་པ། མངོན་པ་དང་བྱིས་པའི་མཐོང་ཚུལ་དང་ <span lang="en" class="tr-baseline bo-latin">UI</span> ཡི་གེའི་རིགས་མེད་པ་བཅས་ཀྱིས་བོད་སྐད་སྤྱོད་མཁན་གྱི་སྤྱི་ཚོགས་ཀྱིས་རང་ཉིད་ཀྱི་ཡི་གེའི་དོན་དུ་ཐོག་མར་བཟོས་མེད་པའི་ལག་ཆ་དག་བེད་སྤྱོད་བྱེད་དགོས་པར་བཅུག་ཡོད། ཉི་ཧོང་དང་ཀོ་རི་ཡ། ཨ་རབ་ཀྱི་ཡི་གེའི་མ་ལག་ལ་གནས་རིམ་ཀུན་གྱི་སྟེང་གི་ཡི་གེའི་རིགས་བརྒྱ་ཕྲག་མང་པོ་ཡོད་པའི་སྐབས། བོད་ཀྱི་ལས་རིགས་པས་རྙིང་པའི་ཡི་གེ་འགའ་ཙམ་དང་བོད་ཡིག་གི་དམིགས་བསལ་དགོས་མཁོ་རྟོགས་ཐབས་མེད་པའི་ <span lang="en" class="tr-baseline bo-latin">CSS</span> མ་ལག་བེད་སྤྱོད་བྱེད་དགོས་ཀྱི་ཡོད།</p>
              <p class="bo-para tr-jomolhari tr-text-base tr-leading-relaxed tr-guard tr-ligatures" lang="bo">འདི་ནི་དཀའ་ངལ་ཆུང་ཆུང་ཞིག་མིན། འདིས་གང་བཟོས་པ། གང་དཔར་བསྐྲུན་པ། སུས་རང་སྐད་ཀྱི་གློག་བརྙན་ཚེ་སྲོག་ལ་ཞུགས་ཐུབ་པ་བཅས་ལ་དབང་སྒྱུར་བཏང་གི་ཡོད། མཛེས་པོའི་སྒོ་ནས་མངོན་པར་སྣང་མི་ཐུབ་པའི་ཡི་གེ་ནི་བེད་སྤྱོད་བྱེད་ཀྱི་མེད། བརྙན་ཡོལ་སྟེང་ནས་མེད་པར་འགྲོ་བའི་སྐད་ནི་བྱིས་པ་ནས་མེད་པར་འགྲོ་གི་ཡོད།</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="story-divider"></div>

        <h2>What We're Building</h2>
        <p>Terma Foundry was founded to close this gap. Working alongside Jamyang Dorjee — a master Tibetan calligrapher with decades of practice — and a team of linguists, type designers, font engineers, and Unicode specialists, we are developing the infrastructure layer that has been missing:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>termaUI</strong> — the world's first CSS framework purpose-built for Tibetan script, solving rendering, layout, and typography with a single stylesheet. A working prototype powers this entire website today.</li>
          <li><strong>An original typeface library</strong> — digitizing Jamyang Dorjee's calligraphic work into production-ready WOFF2 fonts across Uchen, Drutsa, and display styles, covering educational, devotional, and modern registers.</li>
          <li><strong>Open layout tools</strong> — pecha manuscript layout, mixed-language composition utilities, and optical scale corrections that no existing tool provides.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>This work is already underway. The prototype is real, tested, and public. What funding enables is completion: full production release, expanded font coverage, documentation, and the community infrastructure to sustain it as an open standard.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-mission-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="mission-label">Our Mission</div>
        <div class="mission-quote tr-jomolhari tr-text-saffron tr-guard" lang="bo">
          བོད་ཡིག་རྒྱལ་ཁབ་ཡོངས་ལ་གདར་ཤིས་སྦར་ཀ།
        </div>
        <p class="mission-en">"To ensure the Tibetan script thrives in the modern world while honoring its timeless heritage."</p>
        <div class="mission-pillars">
          <div class="pillar"><span class="pillar-dot"></span>Close the digital infrastructure gap for Tibetan script</div>
          <div class="pillar"><span class="pillar-dot"></span>Release professional tools as free, open-source public goods</div>
          <div class="pillar"><span class="pillar-dot"></span>Bridge living calligraphic tradition with modern type practice</div>
          <div class="pillar"><span class="pillar-dot"></span>Put world-class Tibetan typography within reach of any developer</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" style="max-width:1100px; margin: 0 auto;">

  <!-- TEAM -->
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="section-eyebrow reveal">The Team</div>
    <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Meet the people behind<br>Terma Foundry.</h2>

    <div class="team-grid reveal">
      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <Picture src={jamyangImage} formats={['avif', 'webp']} alt="Jamyang Dorjee" width={400} height={400} />
        </div>
        <div class="team-info">
          <h3 class="team-name">Jamyang Dorjee</h3>
          <div class="team-role">Master Calligrapher & Cultural Advisor</div>
          <p class="team-bio">A renowned master of Tibetan calligraphy with decades of experience and deep cultural wisdom. His work anchors the entire Terma Foundry ecosystem in authenticity — from the letterforms that shape our typefaces to the cultural standards that guide our rendering tools and CSS framework. Known for meticulous craftsmanship and profound understanding of Tibetan heritage, he ensures that every layer of the platform — type, layout, and interaction — honors the spirit of the script.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <Picture src={sonamImage} formats={['avif', 'webp']} alt="Sonam Tsering" width={400} height={400} />
        </div>
        <div class="team-info">
          <h3 class="team-name">Sonam Tsering</h3>
          <div class="team-role">Pedagogy Lead</div>
          <p class="team-bio">Sonam Tsering is the director of the Tibetan language program at Columbia University. Previously at the University of Michigan — where he also taught remotely at Yale and Ohio State — he brings firsthand insight into how Tibetan is taught and learned across institutions today. Originally from Rebgong, and later a founder and editor of Bod kyi Dus bab (Tibet Times) in the exile community in India, Sonam helps ensure that Terma Foundry's tools — from termaUI's rendering to our typeface choices — serve real pedagogical needs and work for learners at every level.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <Picture src={thuptenImage} formats={['avif', 'webp']} alt="Thupten Chakrishar" width={400} height={400} />
        </div>
        <div class="team-info">
          <h3 class="team-name">Thupten Chakrishar</h3>
          <div class="team-role">Founder & Lead Technologist</div>
          <p class="team-bio">A seasoned social entrepreneur and technologist with over two decades blending technology, design, and community service. With a background in software development, media production, and 3D animation, he leads the engineering behind Terma Foundry's ecosystem — from termaUI and its CSS framework to the font pipeline and open-source tooling. Co-founder of the Himalayan Elders Project, he brings the technical vision and dedication needed to build the digital infrastructure Tibetan script has been missing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="team-card team-card--wide">
        <div class="team-photo">
          <Picture src={collabImage} formats={['avif', 'webp']} alt="The extended team — linguists, educators, type designers, font engineers, and Unicode specialists" width={800} height={400} />
        </div>
        <div class="team-info">
          <h3 class="team-name">The Extended Team</h3>
          <div class="team-role">Linguists · Educators · Type Designers · Font Engineers · Unicode Specialists</div>
          <p class="team-bio">Behind every tool is a community. Tibetan linguists and educators — from classroom teachers in Dharamsala to heritage language tutors in New York — test our rendering, review our layout decisions, and validate that the ecosystem works in real classrooms and real workflows. Type designers translate Jamyang Dorjee's calligraphic originals into production-ready digital fonts. Front-end engineers build and maintain termaUI — the CSS framework, JavaScript utilities, and developer tooling that make Tibetan typography work on the modern web. And Unicode specialists ensure full script coverage and standards compliance, because Tibetan's stacked consonants and combining marks must be encoded exactly right for everything else to work.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</SiteLayout>

<style>
  .story-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 360px; gap: 4rem; align-items: start; }
  .story-text h2 { font-size: 1.35rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 2rem 0 .75rem; }
  .story-text h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .story-text p { font-size: .95rem; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-text em { color: var(--accent); font-style: normal; }
  .story-text ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-text li { font-size: .95rem; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: .3rem; }
  .story-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 2.5rem 0; }

  /* Tibetan panel */
  .bo-panel { margin: 1.75rem 0 0; }
  .bo-toggle {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .6rem;
    width: 100%;
    padding: .65rem 1rem;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
    text-align: left;
    transition: background .15s, border-color .15s;
    color: var(--text2);
  }
  .bo-toggle:hover { background: var(--surface2); border-color: var(--accent); }
  .bo-toggle[aria-expanded="true"] {
    border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
    border-bottom-color: transparent;
    background: var(--surface2);
  }
  .bo-toggle-script { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--accent); line-height: 1.8; }
  .bo-toggle-label { font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text2); flex: 1; line-height: 1.8; }
  .bo-toggle-chevron {
    font-size: 1rem; color: var(--muted);
    transition: transform .25s;
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .bo-toggle[aria-expanded="true"] .bo-toggle-chevron { transform: rotate(90deg); }
  .bo-body {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-top: none;
    border-radius: 0 0 10px 10px;
    background: var(--surface);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .bo-toolbar {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: .75rem;
    padding: .6rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--surface2);
  }
  .bo-font-label { font-size: .7rem; color: var(--muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; }
  .bo-font-select {
    font-size: .78rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    cursor: pointer;
    outline: none;
  }
  .bo-font-select:focus { border-color: var(--accent); }
  .bo-powered { margin-left: auto; font-size: .68rem; color: var(--muted); }
  .bo-powered-link { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .bo-powered-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .bo-text { padding: 1.75rem 2rem 1.75rem; }
  .bo-heading { color: var(--accent); margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .bo-para { color: var(--text2); margin: 0 0 2.25rem; }
  .bo-para:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  /* Latin terms inline within Tibetan prose — system font, matched optical size */
  .bo-latin {
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'SFMono-Regular', 'Cascadia Code', monospace;
    font-size: .82em;
    letter-spacing: .03em;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 12%, transparent);
    padding: .1em .35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  /* Drutsa stacking is taller — needs extra breathing room */
  .bo-text[data-font="tr-drutsa"] .bo-para,
  .bo-text[data-font="tr-drutsa"] .bo-heading { line-height: 3.4; }
  /* Monlam also benefits from slightly more leading */
  .bo-text[data-font="tr-monlam"] .bo-para,
  .bo-text[data-font="tr-monlam"] .bo-heading { line-height: 2.8; }

  .story-mission-card {
    position: sticky; top: 80px;
    background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 16px; padding: 2rem; border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
  }
  .mission-label { font-size: .68rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .1em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .mission-quote { font-size: 1.15rem; display: block; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-block: .25em; line-height: 1.9; }
  .mission-en { font-size: .88rem; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-style: italic; }
  .mission-pillars { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem; }
  .pillar { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: .6rem; font-size: .82rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .pillar-dot { width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--accent); margin-top: .42rem; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .team-grid { columns: 3; column-gap: 1.5rem; }
  .team-card--wide { column-span: all; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 340px 1fr; }
  .team-card--wide .team-photo { aspect-ratio: unset; height: 100%; min-height: 220px; }
  .team-card--wide .team-info { padding: 2rem 2.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
  .team-card { break-inside: avoid; display: flex; flex-direction: column; background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 14px; overflow: hidden; transition: background .25s, border-color .25s; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .team-card:hover { background: var(--surface2); border-color: var(--border2); }
  .team-photo { overflow: hidden; aspect-ratio: 1/1; }
  .team-photo img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; object-position: center 20%; display: block; }
  .team-info { padding: 1.5rem; }
  .team-name { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: .25rem; }
  .team-role { font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .07em; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: .85rem; }
  .team-bio { font-size: .88rem; color: var(--text2); line-height: 1.8; }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .story-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .story-mission-card { position: static; }
    .team-grid { columns: 1; }
    .team-photo { aspect-ratio: 1/1; height: auto; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const toggle = document.getElementById('bo-toggle');
  const body   = document.getElementById('bo-body');
  const select = document.getElementById('bo-font-select');
  const paras  = document.querySelectorAll('#bo-text .bo-para, #bo-text .bo-heading');

  const FONTS = ['tr-jomolhari','tr-noto','tr-machine-uni','tr-drutsa','tr-monlam'];

  toggle?.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const open = toggle.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
    toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!open));
    if (open) { body?.setAttribute('hidden', ''); }
    else       { body?.removeAttribute('hidden'); }
  });

  select?.addEventListener('change', () => {
    const chosen = (select as HTMLSelectElement).value;
    paras.forEach(el => {
      FONTS.forEach(f => el.classList.remove(f));
      el.classList.add(chosen);
    });
    document.getElementById('bo-text')?.setAttribute('data-font', chosen);
  });
</script>
